              'Please read these Terms of Service carefully before you start using this Site or any of the Services as they govern your use of the Services. IF YOU DISAGREE WITH THE TERMS OF SERVICE AND CONDITIONS DEFINED IN THIS AGREEMENT, PLEASE DO NOT ACCESS THIS SITE AND DO NOT USE THE SERVICES.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline"><strong>1. Introduction</strong></span> This agreement is between you ("<strong>you" or "your" or "yourself</strong>") and GEX (<strong>"GEX"</strong> <strong>or "we" or "our" or "us</strong>"). By accessing the GEX site ("<strong>Site</strong>"), applying for and registering a GEX account ("<strong>Account</strong>"), or using any other services, products, data, content, or other material available through the Site ("<strong>Services</strong>"), you agree that you have read, accept, and will comply with all terms and conditions of use stated below ("<strong>Terms of Service</strong>" or <strong>"Terms"</strong>). "<strong>GEX</strong>" refers to the company Brokers IO LLC (incorporated under the laws of Georgia, company #431178218, with its registered office at #12 Sulkhan Tsinstadze Street, Tbilisi, 0160, Georgia). By opening an Account, accessing, or using any GEX services, you represent and warrant that:\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>You are at least 18 years old and of legal age to form a binding contract under applicable law;</li>\r\n \t<li>You are a natural person, legal entity, or other organization with full legal capacity and authority to accept these Terms of Service;</li>\r\n \t<li>You have not been previously suspended or removed from using our Services; and</li>\r\n \t<li>You do not currently have an existing GEX Account.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you enter into these Terms of Service on behalf of a legal entity for whom you are an employee or agent, you represent and warrant that you have all necessary rights and authority to bind such legal entity to these Terms of Service, and that you are authorized and have the full capacity to accept these Terms of Service and enter into a transaction related to Digital Assets.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline"><strong>2. Definitions</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline">GEX and/or Company</span>. Brokers IO LLC; the company incorporated under the laws of Georgia with ID #431178218 and with its registered office at Sulkhan Tsinstadze Str. #12, Tbilisi, 0160, Georgia.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline">Account</span>. The contractual arrangement wherein an individual has accepted the GEX\'s Terms of Service, Fee Schedule, and Privacy Policy, AML Policy and received approval to use the Services, including the purchase and sale of Digital Assets, and to perform related Transactions.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline">Buyer(s)</span>. Members that submit an offer for buying Digital Assets through the Services.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline">Member(s)</span>. The Buyers and the Sellers, as well as any holder of an Account.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline">Digital Asset(s)</span>. Digital representation of value that can be digitally traded, or transferred, and can be used for payment or investment purposes. Digital Assets such as cryptocurrencies are a form of Digital Asset designed to work as a medium of exchange that uses strong cryptography to secure financial transactions, control the creation of additional units and verify the transfer of assets. Digital Assets use decentralized control as opposed to centralized digital currencies and central banking systems.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline">External Website(s)</span>. Websites not owned or operated by GEX.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline">Fee(s)</span>. The amount payable to GEX for each Transaction, such as a Purchase Transaction, and as further defined in the Fee Schedule.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline">Personal Data.</span> Any information related to an identified or identifiable natural person. An identifiable natural person is one who can be directly or indirectly identified, by reference to an identifier such as a name, an identification number, location data and etc., or to one or more factors specific to the physical, cultural or social identity of that natural person.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline">Price</span>. The "price per coin" for which Members are willing to buy or sell Digital Assets. The Price may be expressed in any of the currencies deposited by Members in their Account and supported by the Services.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline">Seller(s)</span>. Members that submit an offer to sell fiat currencies or Digital Assets through the Services.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline">Service(s)</span>. The technological platform, as well as functional rules and market managed by GEX to permit Sellers and Buyers to purchase and sell Digital Assets. <span style="text-decoration: underline">Site</span>. The GEX exchange platform, as made available on the website: <a href="http://www.gex.ge">www.gex.ge </a>\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline">Transaction</span>. Includes as follows:\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>The agreement between the Buyer and the Seller to exchange currencies and Digital Assets through the Services for currencies at an agreed rate ("Purchase Transaction");</li>\r\n \t<li>The exchange of fiat currencies and Digital Assets between Members ("Conversion Transaction");</li>\r\n \t<li>The exchange of Digital Assets between Members ("Transfer Transaction"); and</li>\r\n \t<li>The exchange of fiat currencies among Members ("Currency Transfer Transaction").</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nGEX may not offer all these transaction types at this time.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline">Transaction Price</span>. The total price paid by the Buyer to the Seller for each Transaction performed through the Services.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline"><strong>3. Scope of Services</strong></span> The Services allow registered users of the Services to:\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>Buy or sell Digital Assets from or to other Members in exchange for other Digital Assets, or for fiat currency;</li>\r\n \t<li>Withdraw any fiat currency balance held in your Account;</li>\r\n \t<li>Enter into arrangements to store Digital Assets listed on the Site;</li>\r\n \t<li>Transfer Digital Assets to a wallet or other users of such Digital Assets outside the Site;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nYou may be unable to use all functions of the GEX Site or Services depending on your country of residence. It is your sole responsibility to follow the rules and laws in your country of residence and/or country from which you access GEX and the Services. If you agree to and comply with these Terms of Service, GEX gives you the personal, non-exclusive, non-sublicensable, non-transferable, and limited right to enter and use the Site and the Services.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline"><strong>4. Account Verification</strong></span> The registration and use of your Account are subject to verification, as required by law and regulatory obligations to which GEX is subject. You agree to provide us with the information we request for the purposes of identity verification, compliance with know-your-customer (KYC) rules, as well as detection of money laundering, terrorism financing, fraud, or any other financial crime. The information requested may also include your Personal Data (please refer to our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>). By providing us with the information we request, you confirm that it is true and accurate, and you agree to inform us of any changes concerning such information. Your Account will be blocked until we are satisfied with the information you provide, and it is at our sole discretion to determine whether it is enough to validate your Account. Moreover, you will not be allowed to terminate your Account or request the deletion of the Personal Data processed during verification operations.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline"><strong>5. Updates &amp; Notifications</strong></span> We may send you e-mails regarding the Service including notices, updates, and amended Terms. We may also send you e-mails with promotional information and materials regarding GEX\'s products and services that you may unsubscribe from by following instructions provided in the e-mail. GEX may, in its sole discretion, make unscheduled deployments of changes, updates or enhancements to the Service at any time. We may add or remove functionalities or features, and we may discontinue the Service altogether. Depending on your device settings, we may automatically check your version of the App, and automatically download to your device new versions of the App. We will notify you of amendments to these Terms by either: (a) posting the revised terms on our website; (b) sending you an e-mail notification to the e-mail address that you provided to us as part of your account registration; or (c) presenting the revised Terms to you when you log into the Services. It is your responsibility to provide and update your external e-mail address, check for such notices, and make sure our notices have not been trapped by your spam filter. It is your responsibility to periodically revisit these Terms as posted on our website. Any such updated Terms will become effective the earlier of: (a) when you accept them online or offline, or (b) <strong>five (5) days</strong> after we post or e-mail the update, in which case your continued use of any of the Services or failure to cancel your account will indicate your acceptance of the amendment.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline"><strong>6. Security &amp; Rules of Use</strong></span> This Site and the Services are for your personal use only. We closely monitor the security of our Site and Services. By registering on GEX, you agree to provide GEX with up-to-date, accurate, and complete information about yourself, as requested by the registration process, and to keep such information updated. You also agree you will not use any Account other than your own and will not access the Account of any other Member at any time or assist others in obtaining unauthorized access. GEX\'s role is limited to providing you with a platform via the Services under which we act solely as a service provider, as your agent, and in accordance with your instructions for the management and transfer of Digital Assets. We do not store any Digital Assets or other Digital Assets directly, but where you Instruct us to arrange for any Digital Assets or other Digital Assets owned by you (including any bought on your behalf) to be held until we receive further instruction from you to sell or transfer them (with any deposit of Digital Assets and/or Digital Assets being deemed to be such an instruction), we will, acting on your behalf, appoint a third-party as a custodian to hold the relevant Digital Assets or other Digital Assets in accordance with our agency authority (see below). The custodian services will be provided on terms that apply directly between the custodian and you, and which will be made available to you. GEX does not directly provide, charge for, and is not responsible for custodian services. Any issues you have relating to custodian services should be taken up by you with the custodians. However, we may, on your behalf, provide assistance in accordance with our agency authority (see below). Notwithstanding the direct custodial relationship between the custodian and you, if for any reason GEX is held or declared to have any legal or beneficial interest in your Digital Assets or other Digital Assets, GEX will hold on trust for you all such rights, title, and interest which GEX has held or declared to have and will not transfer or sell any Digital Assets or other Digital Assets other than in accordance with your instructions (which includes any instructions mandated by law, regulatory authority, or enforcement agencies). By accepting these Terms of Service, you acknowledge and agree that, in doing so, you instruct us on an irrevocable ongoing basis to undertake all the above-mentioned actions on your behalf. You cannot revoke this ongoing instruction except by closing your Account, in which case it will lapse when your Account is closed. In these Terms of Service, "<strong>Instructions</strong>" means:\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>Instructions received or directed via the Site or as received directly from you in any medium other than via the Site, where GEX has expressly agreed in writing to accept such instructions from you;</li>\r\n \t<li>Acts GEX may take as set out in these Terms of Service or in any other form of documentation establishing the legal relationship between you and GEX; and</li>\r\n \t<li>Instructions mandated by law, regulatory authority, or enforcement agencies.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAs a result of this limited agency relationship, we do not, and you agree that we do not have or acquire any rights, title or interest in any Digital Assets or other Digital Assets that are held on your behalf by a third-party custodian. We are not an intermediary, do not acquire any rights to, title for, or interest in, and do not assume or have any rights or control over any Digital Assets, or other assets, or any other Member assets other than in respect of actions taken in accordance with our agency authority and your Instructions. As a result, we will not transfer or sell any Digital Assets or other assets other than in accordance with your instructions (which includes any instructions mandated by law, regulatory authority, or enforcement agencies). <span class="TextRun SCXW52962394 BCX0" lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW52962394 BCX0">Creating or using Accounts without prior direct authorization from GEX will immediately suspend all such Accounts, as well as all pending offers of purchase or sale. Any attempt to do so or to assist others (</span></span><span class="TextRun SCXW52962394 BCX0" lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun CommentStart SCXW52962394 BCX0">Participants </span></span><span class="TextRun SCXW52962394 BCX0" lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW52962394 BCX0">or otherwise) or to distribute instructions, software, or tools for that purpose will result in the termination of the Accounts of such Participants. Termination is not an exclusive remedy for such breach, and GEX may decide to take further action against you.</span></span><span class="EOP SCXW52962394 BCX0" data-ccp-props="{"> </span> <span class="TextRun SCXW261539918 BCX0" lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW261539918 BCX0">You are responsible for ensuring the confidentiality of your account information, including your password, and protecting your own </span></span><span class="TextRun SCXW261539918 BCX0" lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW261539918 BCX0">D</span></span><span class="TextRun SCXW261539918 BCX0" lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW261539918 BCX0">igital </span></span><span class="TextRun SCXW261539918 BCX0" lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW261539918 BCX0">A</span></span><span class="TextRun SCXW261539918 BCX0" lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW261539918 BCX0">ssets and all activities, including Transactions placed on your account (including all GEX Instructions). Any activity on the Site, operations, orders, Instructions, and operations initiated from your Account or using your password shall be deemed to be (1) done by you and (2) irrevocable after verification using your password or using your Account. If there is suspicious activity associated with your Account, we may, but are not required to, request additional information from you, including authentication documents, and freeze any transactions pending our review. You must comply with these security requirements or decide to terminate your Account. You must immediately notify GEX of any unauthorized use of your Account or password or any other security breach by email to <a href="mailto:support@gex.ge">support@gex.ge</a>. Any Member who breaches these rules may be terminated and subsequently held liable for damages incurred by GEX or any user of the Site and Services.</span></span><span class="EOP SCXW261539918 BCX0" data-ccp-props="{"> </span> You will not directly or indirectly take any designed action, or what might reasonably be expected, to cause or result in the price destabilization or manipulation of Digital Assets that are available on the Site. GEX reserves the right to suspend, delay, or cancel an Instruction or series of Instructions issued by a Member or colluding Members, which, if executed, would result in a price swing of 3% or more of the value of a cryptocurrency available on the Site. GEX reserves the right to determine whether to manage the Fee size if an abnormal Order has appeared or to give instructions to terminate such an Order. You acknowledge that you will only credit your GEX account from a bank account that is in your own name, and that you will instruct payments from your GEX account only to a bank account that is in your own name. We reserve the right to cancel transfers that are made by or sent to third parties.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline"><strong>7. Order &amp; Cancellation Rules</strong></span> <span data-contrast="auto">Once </span><span data-contrast="auto">you </span><span data-contrast="auto">have posted </span><span data-contrast="auto">trading instructions </span><span data-contrast="auto">for using the Services (</span><span data-contrast="auto">an</span> <span data-contrast="auto">"</span><b><span data-contrast="auto">Order</span></b><b><span data-contrast="auto">"</span></b><span data-contrast="auto">), your account will be updated to reflect the open Order and your Order will be included in the GEX order ledger for matching with other users</span><span data-contrast="auto">\'</span><span data-contrast="auto"> </span><span data-contrast="auto">Orders. If all or part of the Order is matched to another User, the Services execute the exchange (</span><span data-contrast="auto">a </span><span data-contrast="auto">"</span><b><span data-contrast="auto">Trade</span></b><span data-contrast="auto">"). Once the </span><span data-contrast="auto">Trade </span><span data-contrast="auto">is complete, your account will be updated to reflect that the Order has been closed because it has been fully completed or updated to reflect any partial fulfillment of the Order. Orders remain open until complete execution or cancellation.</span><span data-ccp-props="{"> </span><span data-ccp-props="{"> </span> <span data-contrast="auto">You may cancel an order initiated through the Services if the cancellation occurs before the Order is matched to </span><span data-contrast="auto">an</span><span data-contrast="auto"> Order from another user. Once an </span><span data-contrast="auto">O</span><span data-contrast="auto">rder has been matched to </span><span data-contrast="auto">an</span><span data-contrast="auto"> Order from another user, you cannot change, withdraw, or revoke the GEX authorization to fulfill that Order. If the Order has been partially matched, you can cancel the un</span><span data-contrast="auto">match</span><span data-contrast="auto">ed part of the Order until the </span><span data-contrast="auto">unmatched </span><span data-contrast="auto">part is matched. GEX reserves the right to reject any cancellation request related to </span><span data-contrast="auto">an</span><span data-contrast="auto"> Order after you submit such an Order. If your account does not have enough digital currency to fulfill the Order, GEX may cancel the entire Order or fulfill a partial </span><span data-contrast="auto">O</span><span data-contrast="auto">rder that may be covered by the digital </span><span data-contrast="auto">currency in your account, in each case after deduction of any Fees payable to GEX in connection with the Trade</span><span data-contrast="auto">.</span><span data-ccp-props="{"> </span> <span data-contrast="auto">In order to </span><span data-contrast="auto">carry out the </span><span data-contrast="auto">Trade</span><span data-contrast="auto">, you authorize GEX t</span><span data-contrast="auto">o </span><span data-contrast="auto">temporar</span><span data-contrast="auto">il</span><span data-contrast="auto">y </span><span data-contrast="auto">tak</span><span data-contrast="auto">e</span><span data-contrast="auto"> </span><span data-contrast="auto">control of the Digital Currency you </span><span data-contrast="auto">dispose </span><span data-contrast="auto">of in the Trade.</span><span data-ccp-props="{"> </span> <span data-contrast="auto">For </span><span data-contrast="auto">more </span><span data-contrast="auto">detailed information, please refer to </span><span data-contrast="auto">the </span><a href="/faq"><span data-contrast="auto">FAQ</span></a><span data-contrast="auto">.</span><span data-ccp-props="{"> </span>'
